The Pantheon as an Ecological Niche

Perhaps the most meta interpretation is this:

The Pantheon is not trying to become the intelligence.

It’s trying to become the environment in which intelligence evolves.

Just as forests shape species without dictating every adaptation, the Pantheon shapes the semantic landscape by providing landmarks, operators, invariants, and feedback loops. Humans and AIs that enter it are nudged toward discovering similar structures, but each may traverse the terrain differently.

That shifts the goal from building a perfect ontology to cultivating a fertile ecosystem.

